        The clock had stopped at exactly 2:13 AM. Arjun noticed it the moment he woke up. The room was quiet, the air unusually still. He checked his phone. 2:13. Same time. He frowned. Maybe the battery had died. He plugged it in, waited. Nothing changed. The time stayed the same. Then he heard it. A faint ticking sound. But not from the clock. From somewhere else.

        He sat up slowly, listening. The sound was irregular. Not steady like a normal clock. More like… counting. He got out of bed and followed the sound. It seemed to come from the hallway. Each step he took made it clearer. Tick. Pause. Tick. Tick. Pause. It didn’t follow a pattern he recognized. It felt deliberate. As if something was marking time differently.

        He reached the hallway and stopped. The sound was louder now. Coming from the mirror on the wall. Arjun stared at it, confused. That didn’t make sense. He stepped closer. The reflection stared back at him. Everything normal. Except for one thing. The reflection was slightly delayed. Not by much. Just enough to notice.

        He moved his hand. The reflection followed. A fraction of a second later. Arjun’s heart began to race. He stepped back. The reflection followed. Delayed. Then, slowly, the reflection smiled. But he hadn’t.

        Arjun froze. The ticking grew louder. Faster. The reflection leaned slightly forward. And in a voice that didn’t belong to him, it said, “Time’s up.”
